# Project Setup Prompts

Reference these prompts using: `@prompt-library/workspace-config/project-setup prompt-name`

## Setup Next.js App

**Use when:** Creating a new Next.js application in the workspace

```
Create a new Next.js application following workspace standards:
1. Initialize package.json with workspace-standard scripts (dev, dev:https, build, lint, test)
2. Configure TypeScript (tsconfig.json) with path aliases (@/*, @/lib/*, etc.)
3. Set up Next.js config (next.config.ts) with security headers and optimizations
4. Configure Tailwind CSS with design system tokens (CSS variables)
5. Set up ESLint and Prettier configurations
6. Create .env.example with required environment variables
7. Set up basic folder structure (app/, lib/, components/, etc.)
8. Configure Vitest for testing
9. Add HTTPS support for local development
10. Verify all configurations match workspace standards

Reference existing apps (Feedric, Markense) for patterns and ensure consistency.
```

## Setup TypeScript Project

**Use when:** Initializing a new TypeScript project (non-Next.js)

```
Initialize a TypeScript project following workspace standards:
1. Create package.json with TypeScript as a dependency
2. Configure tsconfig.json with strict mode and modern ES targets
3. Set up path aliases if applicable (@/*, @/lib/*, etc.)
4. Configure build scripts (build, dev, type-check)
5. Set up ESLint and Prettier for TypeScript
6. Create .gitignore with TypeScript-specific patterns
7. Set up testing framework (Vitest or Jest)
8. Create basic folder structure following workspace patterns
9. Add README with setup instructions
10. Verify TypeScript compilation works correctly

Reference existing TypeScript projects in workspace for patterns.
```

